    "Let ŝ = w 1 w 2...w l-1 denote the prefix of the first l -1 words of s. Given ŝ, humans can predict the last word w l of s according to a conditional probability distribution P (s) = P (w l |ŝ).",
    "Likewise, an LLM consumes the prefix ŝ and computes a conditional probability distribution Q(s) = Q(w l |ŝ) for the last word w l.",
    "Let P{x} be the probability that a sequence x occurs in the training corpus T, and let",
    "Let S be the set of all sequences of length l in the training corpus T.",
